// Inter-city flight routes. Each `hub` is one airport's static metadata —
// id, name, host scene. The hub's *position* (ticket counter pixel coords +
// fly-in arrival pixel coords) is determined at procgen time by the
// airport building that lands in the matching scene; see scenes.json5
// (district config: `airport` carries `min: 1, max: 1`) and the runtime
// registry in `sim/airportPlacements.ts`.
//
// `sceneId` binds the hub 1:1 to the airport spawned in that scene's
// procgen. A scene can host at most one airport under the current model.
//
// `routes` are directed edges: `{ from, to, durationMin, fare }`. Adding a
// new destination = add a hub here and add routes from/to it. The UI is
// fully data-driven — no other plumbing required.

{
  hubs: [
    {
      id: 'startTownAirport',
      nameZh: '冯·布劳恩航天港',
      sceneId: 'startTown',
      description: '冯·布劳恩中心区的航天港售票处。',
    },
    {
      id: 'zumCityAirport',
      nameZh: '祖姆市航天港',
      sceneId: 'zumCity',
      description: 'Side 3 共和国首府的中央航天港售票处。',
    },
  ],

  // Round-trip pair: 6 game-hours (360 min) each way, ¥800 fare.
  routes: [
    {
      from: 'startTownAirport',
      to: 'zumCityAirport',
      durationMin: 360,
      fare: 800,
    },
    {
      from: 'zumCityAirport',
      to: 'startTownAirport',
      durationMin: 360,
      fare: 800,
    },
  ],
}
